%20their%20deactivations.%20The%20workers%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20identified%20by%20their%20names%2C%20fearing%20their%20accounts%20would%20be%20deactivated%20again.%20Here's%20how%20they%20did%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EInstacart's%20shopper%20contract%20contains%20the%20details%20contractors%20need%20to%20file%20for%20arbitration.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Instacart%20shopper%20in%20South%20Dakota%20told%20BI%20that%20they%20were%20deactivated%20last%20year%20after%20logging%20into%20the%20app%20using%20their%20iPad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20phone%20was%20running%20slow%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20restart%20it%2C%20but%20I%20happened%20to%20be%20at%20the%20store%20waiting%20for%20an%20order%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20shopper%20said.%20After%20logging%20out%20of%20the%20Instacart%20app%20on%20their%20phone%2C%20the%20shopper%20logged%20in%20through%20the%20iPad%20for%20a%20few%20minutes.%20They%20logged%20back%20into%20Instacart%20on%20their%20phone%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20days%20later%2C%20Instacart's%20Trust%20and%20Safety%20Team%20emailed%20the%20shopper.%20Their%20account%20had%20been%20deactivated.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20completely%20shocked%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20shopper%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20justification%20from%20a%20Trust%20and%20Safety%20representative%3A%20%26quot%3BAccount%20sharing.%26quot%3B%20The%20worker%20inferred%20that%20Instacart%20had%20interpreted%20the%20iPad%20login%20as%20someone%20else%20using%20their%20account%2C%20they%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstacart%20shoppers%20have%20to%20try%20to%20%26quot%3Bresolve%20any%20disputes%20or%20claims%20amicably%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bby%20providing%2030%20days%20written%20notice%26quot%3B%20before%20they%20file%20for%20arbitration%2C%20according%20to%20the%20service's%20shopper%20contract.%20So%2C%20the%20shopper%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20Instacart's%20legal%20team%20providing%20that%20notice%20and%20asking%20to%20have%20their%20account%20reactivated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thirty%20days%20came%20and%20went%2C%20meaning%20the%20shopper%20could've%20asked%20for%20arbitration.%20But%20a%20few%20days%20later%2C%20they%20got%20good%20news%3A%20Their%20account%20was%20active%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20got%20a%20long%20email%20from%20the%20legal%20department%20pretty%20much%20saying%20that%20this%20was%20my%20final%20warning%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20shopper%20said.%20Instacart%20never%20acknowledged%20its%20mistake%20in%20deactivating%20the%20account%2C%20the%20shopper%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20they're%20back%20to%20work%2C%20the%20shopper%20has%20advice%20for%20others%20whose%20accounts%20have%20been%20frozen%20by%20Instacart.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fshoppers.instacart.com%2Fcontracts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSection%20Nine%20of%20the%20shopper%20contract%3C%2Fa%3E%20tells%20you%20everything%2C%20but%20you%20really%20have%20to%20take%20your%20time%20reading%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20shopper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Instacart%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20company%20deactivates%20shoppers%20for%20%26quot%3Bfraudulent%20activity%2C%20violating%20applicable%20laws%2C%20failing%20to%20meet%20acceptable%20standards%20of%20service%2C%20or%20any%20other%20misuse%20of%20the%20platform.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20a%20shopper%20has%20directly%20appealed%20their%20suspension%20and%2For%20deactivation%20to%20the%20Instacart%20Trust%20%26amp%3B%20Safety%20team%20and%20a%20final%20determination%20on%20the%20appeal%20has%20been%20made%2C%20the%20shopper%20may%20choose%20to%20escalate%20their%20issue%20further%20through%20the%20arbitration%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BArbitration%20is%20fully%20voluntary%20and%20at%20the%20discretion%20of%20the%20shopper.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGig%20workers%20can%20follow%20the%20steps%20for%20arbitration%20and%20still%20have%20to%20wait%20months.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20workers%20get%20back%20on%20their%20gig%20app%20of%20choice%20immediately%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they%20follow%20the%20terms%20of%20their%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Uber%20Eats%20driver%20in%20Oregon%20said%20that%20his%20account%20was%20deactivated%20after%20he%20dropped%20an%20order%20when%20the%20delivery%20address%20changed%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-gig-workers-are-fighting-against-sudden-account-deactivations-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20reported%20last%20year.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Afterward%2C%20his%20account%20was%20suspended%20as%20it%20was%20investigated%20for%20%26quot%3Bfraud%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20never%20found%20out%20what%20fraud%20Uber%20believed%20was%20taking%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20couple%20of%20months%2C%20the%20driver%20spoke%20with%20Uber%20agents%20via%20chat%20messages%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20get%20his%20account%20reactivated.%20When%20that%20didn't%20work%2C%20he%20started%20looking%20into%20Uber's%20arbitration%20process%20as%20outlined%20in%20its%20terms%20for%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20involved%20sending%20a%20letter%20asking%20for%20arbitration%20to%20three%20different%20places%3A%20One%20to%20Uber's%20headquarters%2C%20one%20to%20an%20Uber%20email%20specifically%20for%20arbitration%20cases%2C%20and%20another%20copy%20to%20the%20third-party%20arbitration%20office%20that%20Uber%20works%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber's%20driver%20contract%20states%20they%20can't%20file%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20the%20company%20if%20they%20have%20an%20issue.%20%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20sue%2C%20but%20legally%20I%20signed%20away%20my%20right%20to%20sue%2C%20and%20they%20can%20sue%20me%20back%20for%20suing%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20driver%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20never%20acknowledged%20the%20letters%20that%20the%20driver%20sent%2C%20he%20said.%20But%20a%20few%20months%20later%2C%20he%20tried%20downloading%20the%20app%20again%20and%20discovered%20he%20was%20back%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20waiting%20for%20me%20to%20log%20in%20to%20tell%20me%20that%20I%20could%20log%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20A%20company%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20last%20fall%3A%20%26quot%3BRemoving%20a%20driver's%20access%20to%20the%20Uber%20platform%20is%20a%20serious%20decision%2C%20and%20we%20do%20not%20take%20it%20lightly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20Instacart%2C%20Uber%20Eats%2C%20DoorDash%2C%20or%20another%20gig%20delivery%20service%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20abitter%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-workers-explain-how-to-get-reactivated-uber-eats-instacart-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708077601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cd29196fcb546d2d4fe5d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-workers-explain-how-to-get-reactivated-uber-eats-instacart-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gig%20workers%20for%20Instacart%20and%20Uber%20Eats%20who've%20been%20deactivated%20can%20ask%20the%20companies%20for%20arbitration%20under%20a%20clause%20in%20their%20contracts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-workers-explain-how-to-get-reactivated-uber-eats-instacart-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Theater%20Veteran%20Annie%20Baker%20Turns%20to%20Film%20With%20Berlin%20Festival%20Title%20%E2%80%99Janet%20Planet%E2%80%99%20Starring%20Julianne%20Nicholson%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708077600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F