l%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%20%7C%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Was%20a%20Scheme%20to%20Strangle%20Democracy%20With%3A%20Kapil%20Sibal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16145903%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-16-at-13.12.32.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20delivered%20its%20verdict%20on%20Thursday%2C%20February%2015%2C%20on%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%20A%20five-member%20constitution%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20had%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20in%20November%20last%20year%2C%20which%20was%20delivered%20by%20the%20court%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20stated%20that%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds%20are%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20Article%2019(1)(A).%20Additionally%2C%20the%20court%20ruled%20that%20electoral%20bonds%20violate%20the%20right%20to%20information%2C%20asserting%20that%20voters%20in%20the%20country%20should%20have%20information%20about%20those%20who%20donate%20to%20political%20parties.%20It%20is%20against%20the%20rules%20to%20withhold%20information%20about%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20lawyer%20Kapil%20Sibal%20remarked%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20decision%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20historical.%20According%20to%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20every%20citizen%20of%20India%20has%20the%20right%20to%20know%20who%20has%20donated%20to%20which%20political%20party%20and%20how%20much.%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20further%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20the%20financial%20transparency%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%2C%20suggesting%20that%20if%20the%20opposition%20comes%20together%20and%20raises%20this%20issue%20and%20makes%20it%20a%20national%20campaign%2C%20the%20opposition%20may%20benefit%20from%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20introduced%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20in%20early%202018.%20Through%20this%20scheme%2C%20companies%20and%20individuals%20in%20India%20can%20make%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20spoke%20to%20social%20activist%20Anjali%20Bhardwaj%20on%20this%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20one%20donates%20to%20a%20political%20party%20without%20any%20reason.%20Whoever%20donates%20wants%20the%20political%20party%20to%20work%20for%20them.%20The%20common%20people%20need%20to%20know%20from%20whom%20and%20how%20much%20money%20the%20party%20is%20taking.%20But%20this%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20was%20an%20attack%20on%20the%20right%20to%20information.%E2%80%99%20She%20further%20said%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20banned%20this%20scheme%20by%20declaring%20it%20unconstitutional.%20So%2C%20this%20is%20a%20victory%20for%20people%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20information.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FHmikikixouY%3Fsi%3DweMutou_B1crDKcA%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708075800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16145903%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-16-at-13.12.32.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwatch-electoral-bonds-were-a-scheme-to-strangle-democracy-with-kapil-sibal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'No%20one%20donates%20to%20a%20political%20party%20without%20any%20reason%2C'%20activist%20Anjali%20Bhardwaj%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwatch-electoral-bonds-were-a-scheme-to-strangle-democracy-with-kapil-sibal%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22t