and%20writing%20personal%20essays.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Tina%20Freese%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F341947%2Funiversity-admission-counselling-abroad-ambitio-startup-ai-dream-college-uk-us-canada-iit%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20methane%20well%20that%20leaked%20for%206%20months%20has%20released%20a%20year's%20worth%20of%20emissions%20for%20791%2C000%20cars%3A%20report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225102%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Methane%20well%20pumpjacks.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ceeb59f533b039a8845f5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223213%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMethane%20well%20pumpjacks.%20A%20methane%20well%20leak%20occurred%20over%206%20months%20in%20Kazakhstan%20in%202023.%3Cp%3EMario%20Tama%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20well%20in%20Kazakhstan%20leaked%20140%2C000%20tons%20of%20methane%20into%20Earth's%20atmosphere%20in%202023%2C%20scientists%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThat's%20equal%20to%20nearly%20enough%20gas%20for%20nearly%20800%2C000%20cars%20over%20a%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMethane%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20about%2028%20times%20more%20potent%20than%20carbon%20dioxide%20in%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20methane%20well%20in%20Kazakhstan%20is%20estimated%20to%20have%20released%20140%2C000%20tons%20of%20gas%20into%20Earth's%20atmosphere%2C%20as%20it%20leaked%20for%20205%20days%20in%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20worst-ever%20blowouts%2C%20environmental%20scientists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20figures%20were%20reported%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feartharxiv.org%2Frepository%2Fview%2F6709%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epre-print%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20research%20teams%20from%20France%2C%20Spain%2C%20and%20the%20Netherlands.%20It%20was%20released%20on%20Tuesday%20but%20has%20not%20been%20peer-reviewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20BBC%20also%20published%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68166298%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20analysis%20on%20Thursday%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20scientists'%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20satellite%20data%2C%20the%20scientists%20said%20they%20documented%20some%20127%2C000%20metric%20tons%20of%20methane%20ejected%20in%20the%20Karaturun%20East%20oil%20field%20in%202023%2C%20when%20a%20fire%20there%20lasted%20from%20June%20to%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20amount%20of%20methane%20is%20equal%20to%20emissions%20from%20791%2C318%20gas-powered%20cars%20being%20driven%20over%20a%20year%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fenergy%2Fgreenhouse-gas-equivalencies-calculator%23results%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnvironment%20Protection%20Agency%20website's%20calculators.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMethane%20is%20estimated%20to%20have%20around%2028%20times%20more%20global%20warming%20potential%20than%20carbon%20dioxide.%20It%20also%20accounts%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Fglobal-methane-tracker-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E30%25%20of%20the%20world's%20rise%20in%20temperatures%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Karaturun%20leak%20began%20during%20exploration%20drilling%20at%20the%20well%20on%20June%209%2C%20when%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-08-03%2Fgiant-methane-leak-in-kazakhstan-shows-climate-risk-of-gas-exploration%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblowout%20created%20a%2032-foot-high%20fire%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%2050-foot-wide%20crater%20that%20made%20it%20difficult%20to%20seal%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20eventually%20plugged%20on%20December%2025%20when%20well%20operator%20Buzachi%20Neft%20injected%20drilling%20mud%20into%20the%20wellbore%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.upstreamonline.com%2Fsafety%2Fkazakh-operator-halts-gas-fire-at-well-that-has-been-burning-since-june%2F2-1-1576636%3Fzephr_sso_ott%3DODBzqL%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20oil%20and%20gas%20newspaper%20Upstream.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20in%20Europe%20said%20it's%20often%20difficult%20to%20measure%20how%20much%20gas%20is%20released%20in%20remote%20leaks%20like%20this%20one%2C%20and%20that%20they%20showed%20how%20satellite%20data%20could%20be%20effective%20in%20assessing%20the%20damage%20or%20in%20discovering%20unreported%20leaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20detected%20115%20methane%20emissions%20over%20the%20six%20months%20of%20the%20Kazakh%20leak%2C%20their%20analysis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Kazakh%20leak%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20disastrous%20ever%20recorded%2C%20according%20to%20Luis%20Guanter%20of%20the%20Polytechnic%20University%20of%20Valencia%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20research%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20the%20BBC%20that%20%26quot%3Bonly%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnord-stream-pipelines-attacked-remote-explosives-uk-intelligence-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENord%20Stream%20sabotage%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20have%20led%20to%20a%20stronger%20leak.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuzachi%20Neft%2C%20the%20operator%20of%20the%20well%2C%20denied%20to%20the%20outlet%20that%20such%20a%20vast%20amount%20of%20methane%20was%20leaked%2C%20saying%20only%20a%20%26quot%3Bnegligible%26quot%3B%20amount%20was%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuzachi%20Neft%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmethane-spill-released-year-worth-gas-cars-kazakhstan-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708062464000%2C%22visual