r%20Arun%20Jaitley%2C%20%E2%80%9Crepeatedly%20defended%20an%20unconstitutional%20decision%20of%20introducing%20the%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20subverting%20the%20reservations%20of%20the%20RBI%2C%20Election%20Commission%2C%20Parliament%20of%20India%2C%20Opposition%2C%20and%20the%20people%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20that%20the%20massive%20corrupt%20mechanism%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20been%20exposed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20itself%2C%20will%20the%20Modi%20government%20now%20send%20the%20ED%20%5BEnforcement%20Directorate%5D%20to%20probe%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scam%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20declaring%20the%20scheme%20unconstitutional%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20it%20violative%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20and%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20asked%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20to%20furnish%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(EC)%20the%20details%20of%20donations%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20%E2%80%93%20which%20would%20presumably%20include%20that%20of%20donors%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20details%20of%20the%20political%20parties%20that%20received%20the%20contributions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20those%20that%20challenged%20the%20scheme%20in%20the%20apex%20court%20are%20Congress%20leader%20Jaya%20Thakur%2C%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20and%20the%20non-governmental%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20said%20that%20the%20party%20had%20called%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%9Copaque%20and%20undemocratic%E2%80%9D%20when%20it%20was%20launched.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20welcome%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20today%2C%20which%20has%20struck%20down%20this%20%E2%80%98Black%20Money%20Conversion%E2%80%99%20scheme%20of%20the%20Modi%20Govt%2C%20calling%20it%20%E2%80%98Unconstitutional%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EOn%20the%20day%20of%20the%20launching%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20scheme%20the%20Congress%20party%20had%20called%20it%20opaque%20and%20undemocratic.%20Subsequently%20in%20its%202019%20Manifesto%20Congress%20Party%20promised%20to%20scrap%20Modi%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20dubious%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20welcome%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20today%2C%20which%20has%20struck%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20(%40kharge)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkharge%2Fstatus%2F1758023559992246601%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EFebruary%2015%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20remember%20how%20the%20Modi%20Govt%2C%20PMO%20%5BPrime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%5D%20and%20FM%20%5Bfinance%20minister%5D%20bulldozed%20every%20institution%20%E2%80%93%20RBI%2C%20Election%20Commission%2C%20Parliament%20and%20Opposition%20to%20fill%20%5Bthe%5D%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20coffers.%20No%20wonder%2095%25%20of%20the%20funding%20under%20this%20scheme%20was%20received%20by%20BJP.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20lack%20of%20transparency%20in%20the%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%2C%20amplified%20with%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20has%20been%20a%20point%20of%20contention%20between%20opposition%20parties%20and%20activists%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20and%20the%20government%20on%20the%20other.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-received-almost-90-of-all-corporate-donations-to-political-parties-in-2022-23%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%20by%20the%20ADR%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20was%20also%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20case%2C%20the%20BJP%20received%20nearly%2090%25%20of%20all%20corporate%20donations%20in%20the%20financial%20year%202022-23.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20has%20also%20welcomed%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20calling%20it%20important%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20democracy%20and%20transparency.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20very%20important%20for%20democracy%20to%20have%20transparency%20as%20to%20who%20is%20donating%20to%20which%20political%20party.%20It%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20happiness%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20asked%20the%20%5BEC%5D%20to%20immediately%20tell%20which%20party%20got%20%5Bdonations%5D%20from%20where%20and%20how%20many%20electoral%20bonds%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Delhi%20minister%20and%20AAP%20MLA%20Atishi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20citizen%20has%20the%20right%20to%20know%20whether%20the%20party%20in%20power%20at%20the%20Centre%20or%20in%20the%20state%20is%20taking%20decisions%20for%20the%20voters%20or%20for%20the%20donors.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Part%20of%20Secret%20Ballot%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20the%20Modi%20Govt%20Backed%20Electoral%20Bonds%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpim.org%2Fpressbriefs%2Fhistoric-verdict%5C%22%3Epolitburo%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20also%20a%20petitioner%20in%20the%20case%2C%20said%20that%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20on%20Thursday%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20unscrupulous%20scheme%20designed%20to%20finance%20the%20ruling%20party%20by%20anonymous%20corporate%20donors%20has%20been%20completely%20scrapped%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20had%20said%20%E2%80%9Cat%20the%20outset%E2%80%9D%20that%20it%20would%20not%20accept%20electoral%20bonds%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20they%20%E2%80%98legalise%20corruption%E2%80%99%2C%20its%20statement%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20essential%20now%20that%20reforms%20for%20political%20and%20electoral%20funding%20are%20introduced%20to%20ensure%20transparency%2C%20clean%20funding%20and%20a%20level%20playing%20field%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20continued%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20spokesperson%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20Saket%20Gokhale%20said%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20it%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20welcome%20order%E2%80%9D%20as%20%E2%80%9Celectoral%20bonds%20brought%20in%20opaque%20political%20funding%20contrary%20to%20the%20BJP%20government%E2%80%99s%20claims%20of%20transparency.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGokhale%20said%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20holding%20that%20the%20scheme%20violates%20the%20right%20to%20information%20is%20the%20biggest%20win%20in%20its%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20BJP%20could%20see%20who%20was%20donating%20what%20amount%20to%20through%20its%20access%20to%20the%20SBI%20and%20Income%20Tax%20department%2C%20the%20general%20public%20could%20not.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20data%20from%20political%20parties%20show%20that%20not%20just%20the%20BJP%2C%20but%20almost%20all%20political%20parties%20have%20relied%20heavily%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20for%20their%20funding%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20report%20by%20the%20ADR%20said%20that%20while%20other%20national%20political%20parties%20reported%20a%20combined%20corporate%20donation%20of%20nearly%20Rs%2070%20crore%2C%20the%20BJP%20received%20Rs%20610.491%20crore%20from%20the%20sector.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20ADR%20report%20also%20highlighted%20that%20of%20the%20total%20donations%20declared%20by%20the%20national%20parties%20for%202022-23%20(Rs%20850.438%20crore)%2C%20Rs%20719.858%20crore%20went%20to%20the%20BJP%20alone.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20annual%20audit%20report%20of%20the%20BJP%20made%20public%20by%20the%20EC%2C%20the%20BJP%20received%20Rs%201%2C294.14%20crore%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20in%202022-23%2C%20which%20was%20nearly%2054%25%20of%20its%20total%20income%20during%20the%20year%2C%20and%20seven%20times%20higher%20than%20that%20of%20its%20main%20rival%2C%20the%20Congress%20party%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2F54-of-bjps-total-income-came-from-electoral-bonds%2Farticle67829420.ece%2Famp%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3EElectoral%20Bonds%20Are%20Illegal%20Now.%20But%20Who%20Benefitted%20for%20the%206%2B%20Years%20They%20Lasted%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFive%20regional%20parties%2C%20including%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%2C%20the%20TMC%2C%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%20and%20the%20YSR%20Congress%20Party%20(YSCRP)%20together%20received%20Rs%201%2C243%20crore%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20in%202022-23%20according%20to%20annual%20audit%20reports%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Ffive-regional-parties-together-got-over-rs-1200-crore-in-electoral-bonds-in-2022-23%2Farticleshow%2F106032800.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndividually%2C%20electoral%20bonds%20contributed%20to%2097%25%20of%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%2C%2086%25%20of%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%E2%80%99s%2C%2084%25%20of%20the%20BJD%E2%80%99s%2C%2070%25%20of%20the%20YSRCP%E2%80%99s%20and%2071%25%20of%20the%20BRS%E2%80%99s%20total%20receipts%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGokhale%20said%20that%20while%20all%20political%20parties%20benefitted%20from%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20the%20percentile%20numbers%20cannot%20be%20compared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20system%20that%20is%20legally%20put%20in%20place%2C%20parties%20cannot%20tell%20donors%20to%20contribute%20in%20this%20way.%20We%20did%20not%20bring%20this%20policy.%20Contributing%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20is%20the%20choice%20of%20the%20donor.%20But%20at%20no%20point%20have%20we%20supported%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20right%20from%20the%20beginning.%20If%20the%20option%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20been%20given%20by%20the%20BJP%2C%20then%20donors%20would%20use%20regular%20means%20as%20they%20were%20before%20electoral%20bonds%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Even%20donors%20wanted%20secrecy%E2%80%99%3A%20BJP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20sought%20to%20downplay%20the%20judgement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAddressing%20a%20press%20conference%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Thursday%20evening%2C%20former%20Union%20minister%20and%20BJP%20spokesperson%20Ravi%20Shankar%20Prasad%20said%20that%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20was%20brought%20in%20to%20bring%20in%20transparency.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20was%20brought%20in%20for%20a%20very%20laudable%20objective%20%E2%80%93%20to%20bring%20in%20transparency%20in%20electoral%20funding%2C%20and%20to%20reduce%20the%20inflow%20of%20cash%20during%20elections.%20Even%20the%20donors%20wanted%20secrecy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHitting%20back%20at%20the%20Congress%2C%20Prasad%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Congress%20has%20allegedly%20said%20that%20it%20was%20a%20means%20for%20taking%20bribes%20%E2%80%93%20those%20whose%20DNA%20is%20made%20of%20corruption%2C%20please%20don%E2%80%99t%20make%20allegations%20against%20the%20BJP.%20Those%20who%20talk%20about%20level%20playing%20fields%20are%20those%20who%20are%20often%20not%20even%20in%20the%20playing%20field%20in%20elections%20and%20are%20unable%20to%20win%20even%20one%20seat.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708005644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15185313%2FOpposition-II.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fopposition-hails-supreme-court-order-striking-down-electoral-bonds%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20BJP%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20has%20said%20that%20while%20it%20respects%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20the%20scheme%20was%20brought%20in%20to%20bring%20%E2%80%9Ctransparency%E2%80%9D%20in%20electoral%20funding.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fopposition-hails-supreme-court-order-striking-down-electoral-bonds%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%20Doha%20Meeting%2C%20PM%20Modi%20Expresses%20'Deep%20Appreciation'%20to%20Qatar%20Emir%20for%20Release%20of%208%20Indians%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15191615%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-7.15.29.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Less%20than%20a%20week%20after%20eight%20Indians%20were%20released%20by%20a%20pardon%20from%20the%20Qatari%20leader%2C%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20was%20in%20Doha%20and%20thanked%20him%20for%20the%20return%20of%20the%20former%20navy%20veterans%20who%20were%20imprisoned%20for%20more%20than%2018%20months.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThree%20days%20ago%2C%20the%20Indian%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fqatar-emir-pardons-navy-indians-released%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eannounced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20eight%20former%20Indian%20naval%20officers%2C%20who%20had%20been%20arrested%20in%20August%202022%20and%20then%20sentenced%20to%20death%2C%20have%20been%20released%20due%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdecision%20by%20the%20Amir%20of%20the%20State%20of%20Qatar%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20avoided%20explicitly%20using%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98pardon%E2%80%99%20in%20its%20public%20statements%2C%20yet%20the%20premature%20release%20of%20the%20men%20before%20their%20legal%20proceedings%20concluded%20spoke%20volumes%20about%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20visit%20of%20the%20Indian%20PM%20to%20Qatar%20was%20publicly%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnavy-veterans-release-narendra-modi-qatar%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eannounced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20same%20day%2C%20but%20the%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20pointed%20out%20that%20discussions%20regarding%20such%20high-level%20visits%20typically%20occur%20%E2%80%9Cmonths%20in%20advance%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20while%20India%20and%20the%20UAE%20signed%20over%20eight%20agreements%20during%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20no%20deals%20were%20finalised%20in%20Qatar%2C%20despite%20the%20usual%20practice%20of%20negotiating%20agreements%20beforehand%20to%20ensure%20deliverables%20in%20a%20significant%20bilateral%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%20arrived%20in%20Doha%20on%20the%20night%20of%20February%2014%20after%20a%20two-day%20visit%20to%20neighbouring%20United%20Arab%20Emirates.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20a%20ceremonial%20welcome%20at%20the%20royal%20palace%20today%2C%20February%2015%2C%20Modi%20met%20with%20the%20Amir%20of%20Qatar%2C%20Sheikh%20Tamim%20Bin%20Hamad%20for%20delegation-level%20and%20restricted%20talks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHad%20a%20wonderful%20meeting%20with%20HH%20Sheikh%20%40TamimBinHamad.%20We%20reviewed%20the%20full%20range%20of%20India-Qatar%20relations%20and%20discussed%20ways%20to%20deepen%20cooperation%20across%20various%20sectors.%20Our%20nations%20also%20look%20forward%20to%20collaborating%20in%20futuristic%20sectors%20which%20will%20benefit%20our%20planet%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1758079987843035240%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Modi%20posted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20his%20account%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20neither%20Modi%20(on%20X)%20nor%20the%20MEA%20(in%20the%20press%20release%20on%20the%20meeting)%20mentioned%20this%2C%20the%20Indian%20foreign%20secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20expressed%20his%20gratitude.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20prime%20minister%20thanked%20the%20Emir%20for%20his%20support%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20Indian%20community%2C%20and%20in%20this%20regard%2C%20expressed%20his%20deep%20appreciation%20to%20the%20Emir%20for%20the%20release%20of%20eight%20Indian%20nationals%20of%20Al-Dahra%20company.%20We%20are%20extremely%20gratified%20to%20see%20them%20back%20in%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20reporters%20at%20a%20media%20briefing%20in%20Doha.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWorking%20for%20the%20now-defunct%20Omani%20private%20company%20Dahra%20Global%20Technologies%20and%20Consultancy%20Services%2C%20the%20eight%20former%20Indian%20naval%20officers%20were%20tasked%20with%20providing%20training%20and%20related%20services%20to%20Qatar%E2%80%99s%20armed%20forces.%20Though%20the%20exact%20charges%20were%20never%20revealed%2C%20media%20reports%20hinted%20at%20potential%20espionage%20allegations%20against%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fqatar-eight-former-indian-navy-officers-handed-death-penalty%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esentenced%20to%20death%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20Qatar%E2%80%99s%20First%20Court%20of%20Instance%20in%20October%2025.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20November%2C%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fqatar-court-accepts-appeal-application-against-death-sentence-to-8-indian-navy-veterans%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eruled%20in%20favour%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20plea%20against%20the%20death%20sentences.%20Subsequently%2C%20on%20December%2028%2C%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fqatar-court-commutes-death-sentence-given-to-eight-indian-navy-veterans%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecommuted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20their%20capital%20punishment%20to%20imprisonment%20for%20different%20durations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EForeign%20secretary%20Kwatra%20mentioned%20that%20the%20talks%20between%20two%20leaders%20delved%20into%20various%20aspects%20of%20bilateral%20cooperation%20and%20emphasised%20the%20importance%20of%20strategic%20investments%20and%20partnerships%20in%20energy%20and%20technology%20sectors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20PM%20also%20invited%20the%20Emir%20of%20Qatar%20to%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%20the%20Emir%2C%20Modi%20also%20called%20on%20his%20father%2C%20the%20former%20Emir%2C%20Hamad%20Bi